The THREADS directive specifies the maximum number of threads which
can be simultaneously active in the system.  A number of threads are
expended by the PM Shell and daemon processes such as the swapper and
critical error handler before any processes are started by the user.

Directive syntax:	THREAD = n  (16-256)

Default value:		64

Multiple occurrences:	No

Affects protected mode:	Yes
			
Affects real mode:	No

Example:		THREADS = 128

